<br>
Here's the recap how the scene w/ smash played out.<br>
<br>
1) Someone posted in General Chat that they were quitting EQ because their RL relationship w/ someone got messed up because of some stuff they were doing in game/message boards.<br>
2) Bunch of people respond and say &quot;Awww, that sucks, you were cool.<br>
3) Smash responds and tells her to get a life and implies she's mentally ill if her RL relationship is affected by stuff that happens in EQ.<br>
4) Bunch of people say &quot;Wow, what a prick&quot;.<br>
5) Someone starts a new thread in Soapbox, accuses Smash of being a prick.<br>
6) Smash responds to Soapbox thread, lobs some insults back at original poster, stuff along the lines of asking the original poster to use his mouth for stuff other than oral sex w/ small children.<br>
7) Bunch of people say &quot;Can we just get rid of him?&quot;<br>
8 )  Smash is banned.<br>
9) Small flame-war ensues as Smash's friends feel he was acting in self-defense.<br>
10) Mods say too bad, he's a troll and shows no respect for people on the board.<br>
11) Smash gets a new IP address, comes back to board to call Jaxy an alcoholic bitch and the rest of the mods Nazis, etc.<br>
12) Smash gets banned again.<br>
13) Repeat steps 11 &amp; 12 two more times.<br>
14) Things die back down.<br>
<br>
So, you're welcome to say that Smash's banning was unfair, especially since someone personally attacked him in Soapbox so at the minimum they both should've been banned.  But even if it were the case that his banning was totally unfair, and that Jaxy was playing favorites to people on the board she cared about, and other posters were egging smash on and baiting him into making bad remarks, that doesn't change item 11 (above) and that squarely removes any chance of the ban being lifted (even if he wanted to come back, which he doesn't, as he thinks we're all nerds).<br>
<br>
So annnnnyways, you're welcome to argue that Ebon Storm was harassing you in Trak's teeth, but that has nothing to do with Smash's original banning, and we're not lifting his ban just so he can come back and comment on it or something <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    If you think he has some great point to make in the whole TT debate, give him a /tell and then make his point for him. <br>
<br>
/shrug.  Droppin out of the Smash portion of this discussion, as I believe everything that there is to be said has been said.<br>
